// TEST: Cross-module comptime dispatch with [norun]
//
// When a [comptime|norun] event is declared in an imported module and
// invoked from user code, comptime_main should generate a comptime_flowN
// call for it in backend_output_emitted.zig.
//
// KNOWN BUG: The frontend doesn't generate comptime_flowN calls when
// the event has [norun] and is cross-module. The event handler IS
// correctly emitted, but comptime_main is empty and never calls it.
// Note: [comptime] alone (without norun) works fine cross-module.
//
// Same-file comptime works: see 210_030_comptime_flows.
// Real-world reproducer: koru-libs/pq/examples/02_sql.kz
//   ~[comptime|norun]pub event sql { conninfo: ..., source: Source }

~import "$app/comptime_lib"

~[comptime] app.comptime_lib:setup(config: "test-config")
| ok _ |> _
